\section{Additional Ablations}
\label{app:sec:AdditionalAblations}
\subsection{Effectiveness of Different Attention Mask Ratio}
\label{app:sec:Effectiveness of Different Attention Mask Ratio}
\input{Tables/Appendix/Ablation_Mask_Ratio}
% 在这一部分，我们进一步检验了mask ratio of Task-Decoupled Attention Masking的影响。我们选择了0.1,0.3,0.5三种mask ratio ，进行SFT 后，测试了不同模型变种在多个benchmark上的表现，结果如表9所示。提高mask ratio 的比例并不能带来显著的性能提高，相反，还会影响模型在复杂线索推理场景（如Video-Holmes）下的表现。结合正文表6，可以说明选择0.1 的 mask ratio 是非常有效的选择，足以缓解注意力涣散问题，提高推理能力。
We further examine the impact of the mask ratio in Task-Decoupled Attention Masking.
We selected three mask ratios: 0.1, 0.3, and 0.5, and after SFT, evaluated the performance of different model variants across multiple benchmarks.
The results are shown in Table~\ref{tab:app:Ablation_Mask_Ratio}. Increasing the mask ratio does not lead to significant performance improvements; on the contrary, it negatively affects the model's performance in complex clue reasoning scenarios (e.g., Video-Holmes).
Combined with Table~\ref{tab:Ablation_AttentionMask} in the main text, this demonstrates that choosing a mask ratio of 0.1 is a highly effective choice, sufficient to alleviate the attention diffusion problem and enhance reasoning capability.
\subsection{Effectiveness of Verifiable Trajectory-Guided Reward}
\label{app:sec:Effectiveness of Verifiable Trajectory-Guided Reward}
\input{Figs/Appendix/Tool_rate_and_validation_acc}
% 为了验证我们提出的Verifiable Trajectory-Guided Reward对模型的工具调用频率的影响,以及最终对准确率造成的影响,我们消融了bonus multiplier内部的两个核心设计(即Hybrid Clue Score与trun decay factor)。图~\ref{fig:app:tool_rate}展示了使用不同变体的Reward进行训练，每个采样的成功工具调用率随训练step的变化趋势。而图~\ref{fig:app:validation_acc}展示了对应不同step下各变体模型在验证集上的准确率。
% 当不使用turn decay factor时（对应图例w/o turn decay factor (RL)），输出采样的工具调用率相较于Ours (RL)出现小幅提升，但模型在不同step的验证集准确率却弱于Ours (RL)。这是因为针对部分全局性语义总结问题，死板地调用工具查看片段反而会干扰模型对于视频的整体语义的判断。因此当线索清晰地出现在整个视频时，模型应当具有能力判别出此问题不需要额外调用工具，并直接进行回答。我们设计的turn decay factor通过规范直接回答/单线索定位回答/多线索定位回答的教师轨迹引导模型面对不同问题采用不同工具调用策略的能力，有效的提升了模型的灵活性与准确性。
% 当不使用Hybrid Clue Score时（对应图例w/o Hybrid Clue Score (RL)），输出采样的工具调用率显著低于Ours (RL)，且模型在不同step的验证集准确率明显弱于Ours (RL)。这是因为一旦失去了hybrid IoU的引导，模型很难精准的定位到回答问题所需的关键线索区间，进而工具调用对模型性能的增益降低，最终导致模型调用工具的倾向性明显减弱。此外，失去Hybrid Clue Score还会导致偏好消失的现象，奖励取值退化成由答案正确性决定，推理路径错误但答案正确的样本被给予和路径正确的样本相同的奖励，这加剧了幻觉的产生。
%此外，还观察到一个有趣的现象：即不使用SFT进行冷启动的情况下，模型在前20个step的工具调用率出现急剧下降又再度回升的现象。这是因为失去SFT冷启动的原版Qwen2.5-VL本身没有工具调用的能力，在训练的早期调用工具反而对模型的准确性产生负面效果，导致模型调用工具的倾向性急剧降低。但经过一定程度的训练后，模型逐步学会了如何使用工具，此时工具调用逐渐转变为对正确率的提升产生正面效果，因此模型在约进行25个step的训练后出现调用工具的频率急剧回升的现象。而预先经过SFT冷启动的模型工具调用频率相对平稳，这突出了使用SFT对工具调用能力进行预初始化的必要性。
To dissect the influence of our Verifiable Trajectory-Guided Reward on tool-use behavior and performance, we ablate the core elements of the bonus multiplier: the Hybrid Clue Score and the turn decay factor. Figure~\ref{fig:app:tool_rate} plots the evolution of effective tool-call rates, while Figure~\ref{fig:app:validation_acc} tracks the validation accuracy.
\textbf{Role of Turn Decay Factor:} Excluding the turn decay factor results in a slightly elevated tool-call rate but compromises accuracy compared to Ours (RL). This counter-intuitive result arises because indiscriminate tool invocation on tasks requiring global semantic synthesis can fragment the context, obscuring holistic understanding. Ideally, models should bypass tool use when global evidence is sufficient. The turn decay factor acts as a critical regularizer, guiding the model to adopt distinct strategies (direct answering or iterative seeking) based on the query type, thus optimizing the trade-off between inspection depth and global coherence.
\textbf{Role of Hybrid Clue Score:} The removal of the Hybrid Clue Score precipitates a drastic drop in both tool-call frequency and accuracy. Lacking spatial supervision, the model fails to localize pivotal clues, rendering tool invocations ineffective and discouraging their use. More critically, this leads to reward ambiguity: the objective function degenerates into a pure correctness check, where spurious trajectories (correct answer, wrong path) are rewarded equally with valid ones. This lack of process constraint significantly aggravates hallucination.
\textbf{Necessity of SFT Cold Start:} Notably, the non-SFT model (Ours (RL)) exhibits a ``dip-and-recover" pattern in tool usage: a sharp decline within the first 20 steps followed by a resurgence. We attribute this to the initial incompetence of the vanilla Qwen2.5-VL model; early tool calls are noisy and detrimental to accuracy, prompting the policy to suppress them. However, as the model internally acquires tool semantics, the behavior shifts from "noise" to "signal," triggering a rapid recovery in usage frequency. Conversely, the stability of Ours (SFT+RL) underscores the vital role of SFT initialization in bypassing this unstable exploration phase and establishing robust tool-use capabilities from the outset.
\subsection{Effectiveness of Training Stage}
\label{app:sec:Effectiveness of Training Stage}
% 消融表：每个训练阶段带来的性能提升
\input{Tables/Appendix/Ablation_Stage}
% 为了验证每个训练阶段对模型带来的性能增益，我们报告了模型经过不同阶段的训练后在各个benchmark上的准确率，相关结果如表\ref{tab:Ablation_Stage}所示。可以发现，在直接对原版Qwen2.5-VL（baseline）应用多轮工具调用提示词后，模型性能相比于直接回答出现了大幅度下降，且回答模式仍集中在直接回答，这说明原版Qwen2.5VL缺乏原生工具调用意识。仅使用SFT数据对Qwen2.5-VL进行监督微调，模型的准确率已经基本恢复到baseline的水平，甚至在部分benchmark上出现了一定程度的超越（如Video-Holmes的准确率从35.6%提升至39.7%，增长3.1%）。仅使用RL数据对Qwen2.5-VL进行强化学习，模型在各个Benchmark上的准确率已经全面超越baseline，但由于缺乏合适的冷启动训练，此时工具调用次数普遍集中在单轮，难以真正学会通过工具调用进行多跳推理。当联合SFT冷启动与RL后训练，模型的表现最好，使得模型真正学会了利用原生交错工具调用进行长视频多跳线索定位与推理。
To validate the contribution of each training phase, we analyze the performance trajectory across varying training stages, with results summarized in Table~\ref{tab:app:Ablation_Stage}. The experiments reveal that directly applying multi-turn tool-use prompts to the off-the-shelf Qwen2.5-VL (baseline) precipitates a significant performance degradation compared to direct answering. Moreover, the model struggles to break free from text-only generation patterns, indicating a fundamental lack of inherent awareness for native tool invocation. The introduction of SFT serves as a critical stabilization step, restoring accuracy to baseline levels and even yielding marginal superiority on certain benchmarks (e.g., Video-Holmes sees a 5.7\% gain, rising from 35.6\% to 41.3\%). Implementing RL in isolation allows the model to comprehensively outperform the baseline. However, in the absence of proper cold-start initialization, interactions are predominantly restricted to simple clue seeking, which prevents the acquisition of complex multi-hop reasoning skills. Ultimately, the synergistic combination of SFT cold-start and RL post-training delivers optimal performance. This pipeline effectively enables the model to master native interleaved tool invocation, facilitating precise multi-hop clue localization and holistic reasoning within long videos.
\subsection{Efficiency Analysis}
\label{app:sec:Efficiency Analysis}
\input{Tables/Appendix/Inference_Time}
To quantify the speed disparity between our native multi-turn tool invocation and the decoupled iterative reasoning paradigm, we benchmarked the average inference latency per sample across different models on the MLVU dataset. The results are presented in Table~\ref{tab:app:InferenceTime}. VideoSeeker achieves an average inference time of 8.6 seconds, representing a significant speedup compared to the decoupled baselines, LOVE-R1 (12.3 seconds) and VideoChat-R1.5 (17.1 seconds). Notably, this efficiency improvement is secured alongside superior performance, with VideoSeeker attaining the highest accuracy of 72.1\%. This efficiency stems from the fundamental architectural differences in context management. Methods like LOVE-R1 and VideoChat-R1.5 decouple the iteration process into discrete, independent single-turn inference steps. Consequently, the heavyweight multimodal context must be re-encoded from scratch at the onset of every turn, imposing a substantial computational burden. In contrast, our approach treats the tool-use trajectory as a continuous multi-turn conversation within a unified shared context. This paradigm naturally supports Key-Value (KV) cache, enabling the model to persist the states of previous historical contexts and only compute the incremental representations for newly retrieved video segments. This design effectively eliminates redundant context encoding, thereby conserving computational resources and significantly accelerating the inference process.
