\section{Limitations and Future Work}
\label{app:sec:LimitationsandFutureWork}
% 上下文窗口和交互深度。 为了保持训练效率并遵守硬件内存限制，我们将最大交互轮数限制为 8。虽然消融实验表明，8 轮通常足以满足当前基准测试的要求，但对于时长极长的视频（例如电影）或需要数十个跳转步骤的复杂查询，这些限制可能会超出模型的容量。当上下文资源耗尽时，模型将被迫结束推理，甚至可能在收集到所有必要证据之前就结束推理。未来的版本可以集成更高效的上下文管理机制，添加错误探索路径的丢弃机制并以较小的代价转化为错误日志，以支持更长的上下文推理。
\textbf{Context Window and Interaction Depth.} To balance training efficiency with hardware memory constraints, we strictly limit the interaction depth to 8 turns. Although empirical results suggest this budget covers most current benchmarks, it may fall short for extreme scenarios, such as analyzing full-length movies or resolving queries that demand deep, multi-hop logical chains. When the context quota is depleted, the model is forced to halt inference, possibly truncating the evidence collection process. To address this, future versions will explore dynamic context management strategies, such as pruning invalid exploration paths and converting them into lightweight error logs. This would allow the model to sustain longer reasoning trajectories without overwhelming memory resources.
% 工具扩展的灵活性。 尽管 VideoSeeker 目前通过 VideoCrop 接口有效地解决了长视频理解中的时空分辨率瓶颈 ，但现有的原生工具调用范式依赖于预定义的静态接口规则 。这种模式在扩展工具集（例如引入 OCR 识别、音频分离或外部知识库检索）时，面临着显著的工程挑战：每一项新功能的引入都需要人工手动设计特定的交互协议与解析逻辑，限制了模型能力的快速迭代。未来的工作可以探索让模型具备直接编写和执行代码的能力（Code-as-Action）。通过允许模型在受控的沙盒环境中自主生成并运行 Python 代码，我们可以在不显著增加底层工程负担的前提下，支持更广泛、更灵活的工具调用模式，从而赋予智能体更强的自主性与泛化能力。
\textbf{Flexibility of Tool Scalability.} While VideoSeeker successfully addresses resolution bottlenecks through the VideoCrop interface, its dependence on static, predefined tool definitions limits scalability. Extending the framework to include diverse utilities (such as OCR, audio separation, or external knowledge bases) poses a substantial engineering burden, as each addition requires manually crafting specific protocols and parsers. To overcome this, we plan to transition towards a Code-as-Action paradigm. By allowing the agent to synthesize and execute Python code within a secure sandbox, we can enable flexible, on-the-fly tool usage. This approach would significantly reduce the engineering overhead associated with new tools while granting the agent superior autonomy and generalization power.


